pr_title: Added support for azure-core ClientOptions in Key Vault client builders.

timeline.message: Added support for `ClientOptions` in Key Vault client builders.

timeline.bodyHTML:
This can be simplified.

Suggested change
Iterable<Header> headers = clientOptions.getHeaders();
if (headers.iterator().hasNext()) {
List<HttpHeader> httpHeaderList = new ArrayList<>();
headers.forEach(header -> httpHeaderList.add(new HttpHeader(header.getName(), header.getValue())));
policies.add(new AddHeadersPolicy(new HttpHeaders(httpHeaderList)));
}
List<HttpHeader> httpHeaderList = new ArrayList<>();
clientOptions.getHeaders().forEach(header -> httpHeaderList.add(new HttpHeader(header.getName(), header.getValue())));
policies.add(new AddHeadersPolicy(new HttpHeaders(httpHeaderList)));
timeline.author: srnagar

timeline.body: Don't need this check.  `forEach()` will be executed only if there are elements in the list. Update this in other builders too.
